Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.20,0:00:02.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suspense and deduction\Ncloses the gap between
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.26,0:00:04.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The love and hatred between two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.07,0:00:05.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mysteries abound. Strange events
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.80,0:00:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan and Heiji. What will Jodie do?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.67,0:00:09.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He sees through the one and only truth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.27,0:00:11.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a child in appearance\Nwith the I.Q. of an adult
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.27,0:00:13.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,nofcase is left unsolved\Nwith Detective Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.27,0:01:51.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori and I have some doubts that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.71,0:01:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jodie, the teacher,\Nbelongs to the Black organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.65,0:01:58.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We went to Jodie's room to see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.58,0:02:06.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, we encountered an unexpected\Nincident at the entrance of her condominium.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.83,0:02:11.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is something like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.76,0:02:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,falling from above?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.67,0:02:26.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man came falling from the 21st floor!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.04,0:02:31.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had the front door been locked?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.38,0:02:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! lilt was locked up tight!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.88,0:02:36.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, this room was locked up...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.95,0:02:39.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So. it must be suicide... 8
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.59,0:02:42.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is what I first thought too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.76,0:02:43.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.33,0:02:47.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until I saw the curtain of\Nthe bedroom window
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.36,0:02:49.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,from where Mr Takai jumped!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.57,0:02:53.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The curtain was tagged down\Nand the curtain rail was bent
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.24,0:02:56.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and a few hooks came off, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.24,0:02:56.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.34,0:02:59.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This shows evidence that\Nhe involuntarily grabbed the curtain
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.64,0:03:01.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when he came close to falling.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.98,0:03:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would someone trying to kill himself do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.78,0:03:08.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So. then this is not suicide\Nbut in fact...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.95,0:03:10.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.02,0:03:15.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a homicide case...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.80,0:03:26.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,English Teacher v.s.\NRenowned Detective of the West" Part ll
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.84,0:03:30.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cont
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.17,0:03:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's also a murder in a locked room,\NIike we so often see in novels or movies!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.31,0:03:38.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But. Jodie...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.88,0:03:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why ae you ere anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.12,0:03:44.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My room is next door to Mr. Takai's.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.22,0:03:47.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.59,0:03:49.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two just came to visit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.99,0:03:53.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And just when we were leaving the building\Nto go out for dinner,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.50,0:03:55.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Takai came falling down in front of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.87,0:03:57.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.40,0:04:00.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hahaha...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.70,0:04:01.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.87,0:04:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So have you solved\Nthis locked room murder mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.14,0:04:07.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.78,0:04:11.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I think the strange mark\Non the window glass
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.51,0:04:14.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,may have something to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.22,0:04:16.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strange mark?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.25,0:04:22.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is a mark like\Nsomething hit it from outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.33,0:04:24.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.13,0:04:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.99,0:04:27.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.16,0:04:27.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.13,0:04:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've finished developing the pictures\Nthat Ms. Shimoda took.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.30,0:04:33.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. that was fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.77,0:04:39.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most are just ordinary photos\Nof the building
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.94,0:04:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but there was aypicture\Nwith a strange figure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.08,0:04:44.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So. we blew up the picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.85,0:04:47.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.25,0:04:49.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.52,0:04:51.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Ma Takai!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.45,0:04:54.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He grabbed the,curtain after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.26,0:04:58.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he's throwing something into the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.73,0:05:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.83,0:05:05.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, then, he threw the cellphone\Nat the window and made the mark on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.97,0:05:07.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did he throw it anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.17,0:05:11.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe a call made him very angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.27,0:05:12.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.84,0:05:14.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shut your mouths!!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.64,0:05:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is police business!!\NYou civilians, don't belong) here!!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.58,0:05:21.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. talk about hot tempered!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.55,0:05:24.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was going 0 ep im UU no anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.92,0:05:28.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hm fed up with those guys.\NHow could this happen to me so frequently.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.86,0:05:31.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet. although it's true\Nthat they may be annoying,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.76,0:05:34.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,for some reason, with them around,\Nthe case is usually solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.96,0:05:35.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh 7!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.96,0:05:37.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.77,0:05:38.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.13,0:05:42.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know in what way the culprit lead\NMr. Takai to jump from the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.00,0:05:49.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All Ms. Shimoda could've done was\Nhock him with the flash of his camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.74,0:05:53.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there was nothing strange about\Nthe mail that Mr. Nakamachi sent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.88,0:05:57.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one left is Mr. Kawakami,\Nwho called him, but .
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.49,0:06:02.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one would jump to death from the window\Nonly because he's told to do so, would he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.69,0:06:04.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another thing that bothers me
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.96,0:06:08.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is the reason why\Nhe threw the cell phone into the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.00,0:06:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A plausible explanation could be\Nthat he left a clue in his cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.77,0:06:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he didn't want it to drop and break.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.14,0:06:21.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the cell phone didn't break\Neven If 1tifell
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.78,0:06:24.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and there were no suspicious letters\Non the screen either...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.02,0:06:28.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.42,0:06:30.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What time is it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.85,0:06:31.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh 2?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.22,0:06:32.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,WHAT TIME
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.12,0:06:33.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,IS IT NOW?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.06,0:06:36.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What time...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.83,0:06:38.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's eight o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.93,0:06:41.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What time do you think it is now,\Nyou dumb dork!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.23,0:06:43.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha. .!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.13,0:06:45.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.80,0:06:46.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.04,0:06:51.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've completely forgotten to meet her!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.81,0:06:53.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you doing. Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.17,0:06:56.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the one who said that you wanted\Nto go try out the delicious restaurant
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.31,0:06:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that Mr. Ootaki told you about!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.25,0:07:01.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry but I don't think I'll make it today...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.35,0:07:04.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey. Heiji! Where're you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.25,0:07:05.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't hear you well!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.12,0:07:07.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H. . I'm in a weak signal a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.86,0:07:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,h... I'm in a weak signal a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.59,0:07:12.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji!? Are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.06,0:07:17.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H...I can't get to where you\Nfrom here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.90,0:07:19.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So. where the heck are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.20,0:07:22.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well... Tokyo. I'm in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.74,0:07:24.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!? Tokyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.24,0:07:25.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.81,0:07:28.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was going to get back to you\Nas soon as I finished what I had to do but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.94,0:07:31.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.78,0:07:35.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You. saidiwe'd meet in front of\Nthe Big Man of Umeda. at 7 o'clock tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.72,0:07:39.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wrote it down in my memo too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.02,0:07:40.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Memo...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.84,0:07:55.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,fl see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.67,0:07:57.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So. that's what it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.04,0:08:00.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.91,0:08:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the murderer is that guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.79,0:08:15.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? An experiment?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.22,0:08:17.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here. right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.16,0:08:19.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.06,0:08:25.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we reenact what the three did before\NMr. Takai fell to his death from the 2187 floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.00,0:08:30.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We may be able to solve the mystery of\Nthe locked room murder quite easily!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.81,0:08:33.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.84,0:08:37.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ms. Shimoda was only taking photos
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.41,0:08:41.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Mr. Nakamachi was only sending mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.25,0:08:45.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that Mr. Kawakami,\Nin his drunken state,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.85,0:08:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,cursed Mr. Takai on the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.56,0:08:51.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it's far from murder
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.26,0:08:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on. Let's give it a try!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.00,0:08:54.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.80,0:08:57.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,yin order to carry out the experiment,\Nwe're missing some things
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.20,0:08:59.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Missing some things?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.83,0:09:01.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What on earth are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.70,0:09:02.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Liquor!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.24,0:09:06.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember, Mr. Takai fell asleep drunk\Nbefore he fell*to his death!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.67,0:09:09.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.31,0:09:12.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who's going to play\Nthe role of the drunk victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.85,0:09:17.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's the problem...\NThe police officer can't drink on duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.82,0:09:19.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That goes without saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.02,0:09:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm under age
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.86,0:09:23.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only person who can play the role is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.66,0:09:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.50,0:09:29.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. Jodie!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.66,0:09:32.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you play the role of the\Ndrunk victim for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.97,0:09:34.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But on one condition...
